<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-2682] UUIDType assumes ByteBuffer has an accessible backing array</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-2682</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m very embarrassed to say this got left out in the UUIDType, but it&apos;s not doing a hasArray() check on the bytebuffers passed to it, causing it to break.  I&apos;ll make a patch to fix it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12507976">CASSANDRA-2682</key>
            <summary>UUIDType assumes ByteBuffer has an accessible backing array</summary>
