                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13037481" author="jbellis" created="Sat, 21 May 2011 23:43:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;looks like converting array access to ByteBuffer.get&lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/information.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; would be a better fix, since you&apos;d avoid an unnecessary copy for direct buffers.  (this is what TimeUUIDType does.)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13037484" author="edanuff" created="Sun, 22 May 2011 00:35:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;New patch that uses ByteBuffer.get() instead of direct array accesses&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
